HOWDY PANTHERS!!!

1. FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL - AUGUST 19TH. WE ARE NOT AFFILIATED WITH BRYAN ISD NOR COLLEGE STATION ISD, SO OUR DATES WILL DIFFER!

2. MEET THE TEACHER NIGHT/BACK TO SCHOOL BASH - Is scheduled for August 15th. Time will be announced later.

3. UNIFORMS - We will call you to set up when to order and pick up.

4. If you have not registered your student for the next coming year - THERE IS STILL TIME! Go to www.thebrazosschool.org to fill out the application.

5. AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAMS - We are hoping to have that information readily available for you on Meet the Teacher night.

6. TRANSPORTATION - You must provide your own transportation for your student.

7. EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES - We have not started nor cut off any sign ups for any extracurricular activities for this upcoming school year. We will have all that information for you at the Meet the Teacher/Back to School Bash.

Thanks for your patience as we get all this information for you.

post_text: Hello Panther Parents. There has been some misunderstanding on our enrollment process. A lot of you have returned the Intent to Enroll, but haven't filled out the application to enroll your student. If you haven't filled out a 14-15 page application online, then you haven't enroll your student for the next academic school year. Please go to http://www.thebrazosschool.org/enrollment-information-bryan-campus to fill out the application. Additionally, because we are a charter school and you are opting to bring your student to our campus, you must fill out the application every year. Your student's enrollment doesn't roll over every year as it would for the school your student is zoned to go to based on their residency. We hope that clears up any questions you may have. We are here to serve and help. Please let us know if you have any questions. Thank you.
shared_text:

Enrollment Information - Bryan Campus
text:
Hello Panther Parents. There has been some misunderstanding on our enrollment process. A lot of you have returned the Intent to Enroll, but haven't filled out the application to enroll your student. If you haven't filled out a 14-15 page application online, then you haven't enroll your student for the next academic school year. Please go to http://www.thebrazosschool.org/enrollment-information-bryan-campus to fill out the application. Additionally, because we are a charter school and you are opting to bring your student to our campus, you must fill out the application every year. Your student's enrollment doesn't roll over every year as it would for the school your student is zoned to go to based on their residency. We hope that clears up any questions you may have. We are here to serve and help. Please let us know if you have any questions. Thank you.

In observance of Labor Day, our campus will be closed on Monday, September 3rd. We will resume normal school activities on Tuesday, September 4th.

To insure the safety of your students, we‚Äôve implemented new student pick-up procedures. Our campus entry gates will remain closed, and after 3:00 P.M., you will not be able to sign out your student unless you have a valid emergency, have proof of a doctor‚Äôs appointment, or have made prior arrangements with our Principal, Mr. Osgood. Pick-up starts at 3:30 at the side of the sanctuary. All vehicles must have the proper car tag to pick up their students. If you have any questions, please call us at 979-774-5032.

post_text:
Happy Birthday Dr. Seuss! We are celebrating one of our favorite author's birthday this week. Check out the following schedule so you can join in on the fun.

Monday - Wear a crazy hat for "Cat in the Hat" Day.

Tuesday - Crazy & Wacky Socks for "Fox in Socks" Day.

Wednesday - Carry a wocket in your pocket (a wocket, or a toy, but nothing with fur) for There's a Wocket in my Pocket" Day.

Thursday - Wear a shirt from a place you've been for "Oh The Places You'll Go!" Day.

Friday - Dress up as your favorite Dr. Seuss character.

Students must wear their uniform Monday - Wednesday. They will still need to wear their khakis on Thursday.
